<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink120-kilavi">
parattai talaimakaṟkuc colliyatu; petumpaip paruvattāḷ oruparattaiyōṭu kūṭi maṟaintu oḻukāniṉṟā ṉeṉpaṟintu talaivi pulantuḻi ittavaṟu enmāṭṭillai; nī ippulaviyai nīkkavēṇṭum eṉṟu tōḻikkut talaimakaṉ kūṟap pulaviyainīkkak karutiyatōḻi avaḷiḷamai kūṟi nakaiyāṭic colliyatūumām </p>    <p xml:lang="en">
Spoken by the other woman to the heroine. It could also be spoken by the confidante while laughing, speaking of her [the other woman’s] youthfulness - [the confidante] having considered getting rid of [her] displeasure as the hero says to the confidante when the heroine is alone, [she] knowing that he goes about, having united with a young[er] lady [and now] disappeared, [the hero saying] ‘this mistake is not because of me. You need to get rid of [your] sorrow’. 

 </p>
            </div>    
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink121">
<l>kaṇṭiku mallamō koṇkaniṉ kēḷē</l>
<l>muṇṭakak kōtai naṉaiyat</l>
<l>teṇṭiraip pauvam pāyntuniṉ ṟōḷē</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>We have seen your friend, haven't we, oh man from the maritime tract?</l>
<l>She who stood [there], having jumped into the ocean with clear waves,</l>
<l>So that her garland of Muṇṭakam flowers became wet.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
